THE CANNONBALL RUN SERIES.

11:35.590 --> 11:37.251
MARY, YOU TAKE HOOPER
THROUGH STROKER ACE.

11:37.290 --> 11:38.552
- THOSE ARE BURT REYNOLDS
MOVIES.

11:39.860 --> 11:43.819
- WELL, WE REALLY HAVE OUR WORK
CUT OUT FOR US THEN.

11:43.870 --> 11:46.839
[dramatic music]

11:46.870 --> 11:52.877
*

12:05.750 --> 12:07.388
- THINK, SHAWN, THINK.

12:07.420 --> 12:09.217
TRY AND FIND SOMETHING.

12:09.260 --> 12:10.818
YOU DIDN'T SEE HIS FACE,

12:10.860 --> 12:14.125
BUT YOU CAN PICK UP
ON SOMETHING.

12:16.200 --> 12:18.464
- YOU CAN DO IT, SHAWN.

12:18.500 --> 12:21.367
THE FEET, THE SHOES.

12:21.400 --> 12:22.435
SOMETHING.

12:25.340 --> 12:27.934
- SPENCER! I'M COLD!

12:27.980 --> 12:30.039
AND HURRY UP.
WE DON'T HAVE ALL NIGHT.

12:33.020 --> 12:35.739
- YOU CAN DO IT, SHAWN.
- COME ON. FOCUS.

12:35.780 --> 12:38.840
THINK. SEE SOMETHING.

12:38.890 --> 12:42.018
SHOW ME YOUR FACE!
LOOK AT ME!

12:42.060 --> 12:43.880
- COME ON, SHAWN,
THE PROJECT IONIST.

12:43.930 --> 12:45.886
WE DIDN'T GET TO THE DRIVE-IN
TILL 11:26.

12:45.930 --> 12:48.524
HOW WOULD YANG HAVE HAD
THE TIME TO DO ALL THAT?

12:54.540 --> 12:56.804
COME ON, SHAWN.
IT'S ME.

12:56.840 --> 12:58.569
IT'S ALWAYS BEEN ME.

13:00.540 --> 13:03.600
- I DON'T THINK WE'RE
SPEAKING TO THE MOUSE.

13:03.650 --> 13:05.402
THE MOUSE IS SPEAKING TO YOU.

13:05.450 --> 13:08.977
I DON'T THINK, SHAWN.
I KNOW.

13:09.020 --> 13:10.544
- SHAWN.

13:10.590 --> 13:12.182
SHAWN!

13:12.220 --> 13:14.085
LOOK WHAT HAPPENED
TO OUR WINDOW.

13:17.360 --> 13:20.329
[Psycho music]

13:20.360 --> 13:23.090
*

13:23.130 --> 13:25.166
- GUS...

13:25.200 --> 13:27.088
I KNOW WHO YIN IS.

13:31.140 --> 13:32.107
- MR. SPENCER,
THIS IS OUTLANDISH.

13:32.140 --> 13:33.300
- JUST HEAR HIM OUT.

13:33.340 --> 13:35.001
- MARY LIGHTLY
ALL BUT CONFESSED

13:35.040 --> 13:37.372
TO GUS AND I WHEN HE SAID
THAT HE HAD SPENT

13:37.410 --> 13:39.776
THE LAST 13 YEARS
OF HIS LIFE WITH YANG

13:39.810 --> 13:42.847
AND HAD NO IDEA WHAT HE WAS
GOING TO DO WITHOUT HER.

13:42.890 --> 13:44.539
- MR. SPENCER,
I HAVE TO ASK:

13:44.590 --> 13:47.889
WHY ARE YOU JUST NOW
RECEIVING THESE PSYCHIC SIGNALS?

13:47.920 --> 13:48.989
WHY DIDN'T YOU TAG MARY
AS A SUSPECT

13:49.020 --> 13:50.055
THE LAST TIME AROUND?

13:50.090 --> 13:51.227
- HE DID.

13:51.260 --> 13:52.386
IT WAS THE FIRST THING HE SAID
WHEN HE SAW HIM.

13:52.430 --> 13:54.125
- OH, HE WAS JUST BEING
FLIPPANT AND JACKASSY.

13:54.160 --> 13:55.957
- LOOK, I THINK OUR TRACK RECORD
SPEAKS FOR ITSELF.

13:56.000 --> 13:57.160
WE CAN EITHER
DO THIS TOGETHER,

13:57.200 --> 13:58.269
OR WE CAN FOLLOW YOU AROUND

13:58.300 --> 13:59.722
AND CONDUCT OUR OWN
INVESTIGATION.

14:02.240 --> 14:04.003
- ALL RIGHT, MR. SPENCER.

14:04.040 --> 14:05.905
BUT YOU'RE ON
A VERY SHORT LEASH.

14:05.940 --> 14:08.431
HOW DO YOU SUGGEST
THAT WE PROCEED?

14:08.480 --> 14:09.777
- KEEPING IN MIND,
OF COURSE,

14:09.810 --> 14:11.368
WE HAVEN'T A SHRED
OF PHYSICAL EVIDENCE.

14:11.410 --> 14:12.604
- WE DO NOTHING.

14:12.650 --> 14:14.709
- NOTHING?
HOW SEINFELDIAN.

14:14.750 --> 14:16.479
- CHIEF, WE LET HIM
HANG HIMSELF.

14:16.520 --> 14:18.715
WE KEEP HIM CLOSE,
WE PLAY ALONG.

14:18.750 --> 14:20.217
WE CATCH HIM RED-HANDED.

14:21.860 --> 14:22.986
[all shout]

14:25.790 --> 14:27.428
- AHEM.

14:27.460 --> 14:30.918
- HELLO...MARY.

14:30.970 --> 14:32.267
- WELL, I GOT YIN'S NEXT CLUE.

14:32.300 --> 14:33.392
I FOUND IT ON MY DOORSTEP,

14:33.440 --> 14:35.192
ALONG WITH A CAN
OF MATIZ GALLEGO SARDINES

14:35.240 --> 14:36.366
IN OLIVE OIL.

14:36.400 --> 14:37.537
IT TOOK EVER OUNCE
OF WILLPOWER I HAD

14:37.570 --> 14:38.537
NOT TO OPEN THEM UP.

14:38.570 --> 14:40.379
- SWEET.
SOCK IT TO US.

14:40.410 --> 14:43.573
- "TAKE 39 STEPS BY 12:05.

14:43.610 --> 14:45.749
"WAIT FOR IIIIT.

14:45.780 --> 14:47.270
"COORDINATES
NORTH BY NORTHWEST.

14:47.320 --> 14:48.776
MAKE A WISH."

14:48.820 --> 14:50.287
- WAIT FOR WHAT?
MORE HITCHCOCK.

14:50.320 --> 14:51.344
- NO, IT'S JUST A MOTIF.

14:51.390 --> 14:52.516
TRY TO THINK THROUGH IT,
CHIEF.

14:52.550 --> 14:54.108
OKAY? HE'S SHOWING OFF.

14:54.160 --> 14:56.958
- WE'RE ALL EARS, LIGHTLY.

14:56.990 --> 14:59.356
- YOU REALLY ARE ALL EARS,
CARLTON.

14:59.390 --> 15:01.119
SPECTACULAR.

15:01.900 --> 15:03.299
WELL, I'VE DELIVERED
THIS CLUE,

15:03.330 --> 15:05.491
AND I SUGGEST THAT WE ALL
THINK ABOUT IT ANALYTICALLY.

15:05.530 --> 15:07.191
- OKAY, NORTHWEST, NORTHWEST.

15:07.240 --> 15:09.060
NORTHWEST MALL,
NORTHWEST AIR.

15:09.100 --> 15:10.362
NORTHWEST...
PARK AND PICNIC.

15:10.410 --> 15:11.809
- THAT'S IT.
- WHAT?

15:11.840 --> 15:14.035
- I PLAY DOMINOES WITH SOME
JAMAICANS THERE ON SUNDAYS.

15:14.080 --> 15:15.672
THERE'S A SET OF STAIRS THAT
LEADS UP TO A PENNY FOUNTAIN.

15:15.710 --> 15:16.734
"MAKE A WISH."

15:16.780 --> 15:18.099
- OKAY, WE HAVE
LESS THAN A HALF HOUR.

15:18.150 --> 15:19.606
MR. LIGHTLY, YOU RIDE
WITH MY DETECT IVES.

15:19.650 --> 15:23.484
LET'S GO!
- WE'LL BE RIGHT BEHIND YOU!

15:23.520 --> 15:25.579
- COME ON,
WE'RE TAKING A DETOUR.

15:28.260 --> 15:30.228
- WE'RE CLOSE.
HIS HOUSE SHOULD BE RIGHT HERE.

15:33.030 --> 15:34.099
THAT'S IT.

15:34.130 --> 15:35.449
THAT'S THE ADDRESS.

15:35.500 --> 15:37.024
- DAMN, MARY.

15:37.070 --> 15:39.959
I THINK MARY WOULD WANT YOU
TO HAVE A CAN OR TWO.

15:40.000 --> 15:41.399
- SHUT UP, SHAWN.
[fly buzzing]

15:45.770 --> 15:48.307
- DUDE, IT'S BEN!

15:48.340 --> 15:49.568
DUDE, HE WASN'T KIDDING.

15:49.610 --> 15:52.443
- THAT HAT BELONGS
IN MY WALLET, SHAWN.

15:52.480 --> 15:57.349
- WHAT'S WITH
ALL THE NUMBERS?

15:57.390 --> 15:58.709
- IT'S PI.

15:58.750 --> 16:00.081
- GUS, DON'T BE
TOPHER GRACE

16:00.120 --> 16:01.781
RUNNING ON THE BEACH
AT THE END OF GOOD COMPANY.

16:01.820 --> 16:03.526
- THE VALUE OF PI, SHAWN,
AS IN MATHEMATICS.

16:03.560 --> 16:06.120
- OH, RIGHT,
WITH THE--YEAH.

16:06.160 --> 16:08.424
DO WE LIKE PI, HE ASKS.

16:08.460 --> 16:09.996
THIS DUDE HAS PROBLEMS.

16:22.380 --> 16:23.904
- UHH!

16:23.950 --> 16:26.601
- QUICK.

16:26.650 --> 16:28.948
- ARREST THAT FAT KID.
[kid laughing]

16:28.980 --> 16:31.119
- THERE'S NO TIME.

16:31.150 --> 16:32.549
- NO, THERE'S LESS
THAN A MINUTE.

16:32.590 --> 16:33.716
DAMN IT, MARY, COME ON!

16:33.760 --> 16:34.909
WHAT ARE YOU WEARING,
ANKLE WEIGHTS?

16:34.960 --> 16:36.052
- OF COURSE I AM!

16:36.090 --> 16:37.887
I'VE GOT A THIGH SPASM!

16:37.930 --> 16:39.955
IT BURNS SO DEEP,
YOU GUYS!

16:39.990 --> 16:42.129
OHH!

16:42.160 --> 16:43.821
GO ON WITHOUT ME!

16:43.870 --> 16:45.963
[whimpering]
- DAMN IT.

16:46.000 --> 16:47.729
- WHAT DO YOU THINK?

16:47.770 --> 16:48.964
- JUST COME ON, MARY!

16:49.000 --> 16:51.264
- DUDE, A TICKET STUB.

16:51.310 --> 16:53.437
HE WAS DEFINITELY
AT THE MOVIE THEATER.

16:53.480 --> 16:54.936
- HE SURE WAS.

16:57.950 --> 16:59.406
UM...

16:59.450 --> 17:00.417
GUS.

17:00.450 --> 17:03.817
- OH, HELL, NO.

17:12.690 --> 17:15.625
- 36, 37, 38, 39.

17:16.800 --> 17:18.222
- IT'S 12:05 ON THE DOT.

17:18.270 --> 17:19.965
WHAT THE HELL ARE WE
SUPPOSED TO BE LOOKING FOR?

17:21.940 --> 17:23.305
- I DON'T...

17:23.340 --> 17:24.898
WAIT.

17:24.940 --> 17:26.635
I THINK I HAVE SOMETHING.

17:26.670 --> 17:27.637
THAT'S THE NORTH LINE.

17:27.680 --> 17:28.669
"NORTH BY NORTHWEST."

17:28.710 --> 17:30.871
THAT'S HIM!

17:33.150 --> 17:34.742
- WHERE THE HELL IS MARY?

17:34.780 --> 17:36.316
SON OF A BITCH!

17:36.350 --> 17:37.339
MCNAB!

17:37.390 --> 17:40.757
- WHAT IS IT?

17:40.790 --> 17:42.678
"IT'S TIME WE MET
IN THE FLESH, DON'T YOU THINK?"

17:42.720 --> 17:43.857
- IT'S HIS NEXT MOVE.

17:43.890 --> 17:45.653
HE'S JUST WORKING OUT
THE WORDING.

17:45.690 --> 17:48.250
- "736 LA PORTE AVENUE,
INDUSTRIAL LANE.

17:48.300 --> 17:49.653
"CURTAIN'S AT 9 PM.

17:49.700 --> 17:51.588
COME ALONE."

17:51.630 --> 17:53.860
WHO IS IT FOR?

17:53.900 --> 17:56.368
- HIS NEXT VICTIM.

17:56.400 --> 17:57.833
- MCNAB, DO NOT TELL ME THAT!

17:57.870 --> 18:00.998
SOMEONE ON THAT BUS
MUST HAVE SEEN SOMETHING.

18:01.040 --> 18:03.406
- HEY! WHAT HAPPENED?
WHERE WERE YOU?

18:03.450 --> 18:04.678
- [talking indistinctly]

18:04.710 --> 18:06.302
- CUT THE CRAP, MARY!
START TALKING!

18:06.350 --> 18:07.419
- DIDN'T YOU SEE
AT THE BUS STOP?

18:07.450 --> 18:08.769
IT WAS HIM!

18:08.820 --> 18:11.084
I TRIED TO STOP HIM, I TRIED,
BUT IT WAS TOO LATE.

18:11.120 --> 18:13.680
HE WAS WEARING A...
VERY STYLISH FEDORA.

18:13.720 --> 18:15.085
- YEAH, WE KNOW.
WE GOT OFF ON THE NEXT STOP.

18:15.120 --> 18:16.451
WE MUST HAVE MISSED HIM
BY A MATTER OF SECONDS.

18:16.490 --> 18:17.684
- OF COURSE YOU DID.

18:17.730 --> 18:19.823
HE KNEW EXACTLY
HOW MUCH TIME IT WOULD TAKE.

18:19.860 --> 18:22.795
HE PROBABLY REHEARSED IT
100 TIMES.

18:22.830 --> 18:24.491
HE TOTALLY MAN HAN DLED ME.

18:24.530 --> 18:25.497
[cell phone ringing]

18:25.530 --> 18:27.498
I DROPPED MY SHOE.
[beep]

18:27.540 --> 18:30.236
- SPENCER WHERE THE HELL
ARE YOU?

18:30.270 --> 18:32.067
YEAH, WELL,
THANKS FOR NOTHING.

18:32.110 --> 18:33.737
- IS SHAWN OKAY?

18:33.780 --> 18:35.099
- HE'S FINE.
HIS TIRE BLEW.

18:35.140 --> 18:36.300
- GET IN THE CAR.

18:44.250 --> 18:47.014
- SHAWN, ARE YOU SURE THIS
IS WHERE WE'RE SUPPOSED TO BE?

18:47.050 --> 18:48.483
- AHEM, ABSOLUTELY.

18:48.520 --> 18:49.919
THIS IS ONE OF THE STRONGEST
VISIONS I'VE HAD IN YEARS.

18:49.960 --> 18:52.622
- "736 LA PORTE AVENUE,
INDUSTRIAL LANE."

18:55.000 --> 18:56.524
I SAW HIS WATCH.

18:56.560 --> 18:58.164
[motorcycle rewing]

19:00.300 --> 19:03.030
LOOK AT THAT.

19:09.680 --> 19:11.500
IT'S SHOW TIME.

19:11.550 --> 19:13.472
- LET'S BAG THIS DEGENERATE.
[guns cock]

19:13.520 --> 19:14.919
YOU TWO STAY PUT.

19:18.550 --> 19:20.108
- OF COURSE IT'S LOCKED.

19:20.150 --> 19:21.287
I'M GONNA TAKE
THE EAST EXIT.

19:21.320 --> 19:22.457
- COPY THAT--
I'LL HEAD AROUND BACK.

19:22.490 --> 19:23.582
TAKE IT FROM BEHIND.

19:23.630 --> 19:25.382
- LET'S TRY AND KEEP
THIS P.G. RATED.

19:25.430 --> 19:27.295
- DAMN IT, SPENCER,
I TOLD YOU TO STAY IN THE CAR.

19:27.330 --> 19:29.321
- I THINK HE'S PROBABLY KEEPING
AN EYE ON THAT DOOR.

19:29.360 --> 19:31.066
- WE KNOW--WE'RE GONNA
WALK THE PERIMETER.

19:31.100 --> 19:32.294
GO BACK TO THE CAR.

19:32.330 --> 19:33.558
THIS DOOR OPENS,
OR YOU SEE ANYTHING

19:33.600 --> 19:35.488
THAT DOESN'T LOOK RIGHT,
HONK THE HORN.

19:35.540 --> 19:36.564
GO, NOW!

19:36.600 --> 19:38.204
- OKAY.

19:47.350 --> 19:48.977
- SHAWN, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

20:00.500 --> 20:01.455
- UH-UH, SHAWN.

20:01.500 --> 20:03.263
WE'RE OUT OF HERE.

20:03.300 --> 20:04.961
[pounding on door]

20:05.000 --> 20:07.389
WE'RE LOCKED IN.

20:07.440 --> 20:08.759
- WHAT ARE WE LOOKING AT?

20:08.800 --> 20:10.267
- I DON'T CARE, SHAWN.

20:10.310 --> 20:13.404
- COME OUT, COME OUT,
WHEREVER YOU ARE.

20:15.280 --> 20:17.601
- WHAT ARE YOU UP TO, MARY?

20:24.990 --> 20:28.050
OH, DUDE, I'M GETTING
SERIOUS DEJA VU RIGHT NOW.

20:28.090 --> 20:29.910
WAIT A MINUTE.

20:32.030 --> 20:33.327
- OH, MY GOSH.

20:33.360 --> 20:34.554
HE'S GONNA
SHOOT SOMEBODY, SHAWN.

20:34.600 --> 20:35.555
HE HAS A GUN.

20:35.600 --> 20:38.467
- OH...NO.

20:39.370 --> 20:40.837
GUS...

20:40.870 --> 20:42.462
THIS IS PSYCHO!
WE WERE WRONG!

20:42.500 --> 20:45.765
MARY IS THE VICTIM.
MARY!

20:45.810 --> 20:47.107
GET OUT OF HERE!

20:50.980 --> 20:52.709
- OHH! GAH!

20:52.750 --> 20:54.570
- THERE'S GOTTA BE
A WAY OUT OF THIS ROOM!

20:56.480 --> 20:58.448
GUS.

20:58.490 --> 21:00.117
[Psycho music]

21:00.150 --> 21:01.458
[gasp5]

21:06.130 --> 21:07.859
MARY!

21:07.900 --> 21:09.322
- WHAT...

21:09.360 --> 21:11.225
- OH!

21:14.100 --> 21:15.829
I'M SORRY, GUS.

21:15.870 --> 21:17.428
- THE CLUE WAS MEANT FOR HIM.

21:17.470 --> 21:19.358
- I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
WHAT ABOUT THE NOTEBOOK?

21:19.410 --> 21:21.537
- ALL RECREATIONS.
NOT FIRST DRAFTS!

21:21.580 --> 21:23.946
- I SHOULD--

21:23.980 --> 21:26.107
I SHOULD HAVE
TOLD YOU GUYS, BUT...

21:26.150 --> 21:28.516
I WANTED TO BE HEROIC.

21:29.350 --> 21:30.317
- AH, MARY.

21:30.350 --> 21:32.545
WITH A FLARE GUN?

21:32.590 --> 21:35.388
- I WAS REALLY COUNTING
ON THE ELEMENT OF SURPRISE.

21:35.420 --> 21:37.058
- THERE...

21:37.090 --> 21:38.626
- SPENCER,
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED?

21:38.660 --> 21:39.752
- THERE!
HE WAS RIGHT THERE!

21:45.800 --> 21:47.529
- COULD YOU TAKE CARE
OF BEN?

21:47.570 --> 21:50.095
- HEY...YOU HANG ON.
THERE'S HELP ON THE WAY.

21:52.870 --> 21:55.373
- DO YOU THINK THEY HAVE
RACQUETBALL IN HEAVEN?

21:58.450 --> 22:00.202
- I KNOW THEY DO.

22:00.250 --> 22:02.810
- [chuckles weakly]

22:23.340 --> 22:25.968
- YOU'RE INTERRUPTING
MY EXERCISE TIME, SHAWN.

22:26.010 --> 22:28.069
I ONLY GET 45 MINUTES A WEEK.

22:28.110 --> 22:29.270
ASIDE FROM SHOCK TREATMENTS,

22:29.310 --> 22:31.175
THIS IS ALL I HAVE
TO LOOK FORWARD TO.

22:31.210 --> 22:32.609
- THAT AND HELL.

22:34.680 --> 22:36.375
- ROLL IT BACK, REGINALD!

22:36.420 --> 22:37.785
- WHO THE HELL
IS SHE TALKING TO?

22:37.820 --> 22:39.981
- LOOK, YOUR PARTNER
WORE ANKLE WEIGHTS

22:40.020 --> 22:41.180
TO THROW ME OFF.

22:41.220 --> 22:42.517
I WAS WRONG ABOUT MARY.

22:42.560 --> 22:44.289
- I KNOW.

22:44.330 --> 22:46.252
SUCH A SHAME.

22:46.290 --> 22:48.121
MY LADY GUARD FRIEND TOLD ME.

22:48.160 --> 22:49.696
PLEASE DON'T
BEAT YOURSELF UP, SHAWN.

22:49.730 --> 22:51.266
THE GUY CREEPED ME OUT.

22:51.300 --> 22:52.619
THIS WAS AN HONEST MISTAKE.

22:52.670 --> 22:55.195
- LOOK, WE NEED YOUR HELP.

22:55.240 --> 22:57.299
- OH, LITTLE BROODING
BROWN ONE.

22:57.340 --> 22:59.558
I'VE ALREADY GIVEN YOU
ALL THE HELP YOU NEED

22:59.610 --> 23:00.736
TO CATCH YIN.

23:00.780 --> 23:03.499
- HOW? YOU JUST SEEM
BAT ASS CRAZY TO ME.

23:03.550 --> 23:05.939
- NEVER...JUDGE A BOOK
BY ITS COVER.

23:05.980 --> 23:08.869
NO MATTER HOW SEXY
THAT PICTURE MIGHT BE.

23:12.490 --> 23:14.253
- [sighs]

23:14.290 --> 23:15.814
GIVE ME THE BOOK.

23:15.860 --> 23:17.657
- SHAWN, I READ THIS BOOK
COVER TO COVER.

23:17.690 --> 23:20.079
I'VE POURED OVER IT.

23:22.700 --> 23:24.793
- COVER TO COVER.

23:24.830 --> 23:26.263
- WHAT?

23:31.410 --> 23:32.399
- LOOK AT THAT.

23:32.440 --> 23:33.532
- NICE.

23:33.580 --> 23:35.172
SHE DREW A SELF-PORTRAIT
JUST FOR YOU.

23:35.210 --> 23:36.199
BUT WHAT DOES IT MEAN?

23:36.240 --> 23:38.208
[cell phone ringing]

23:38.850 --> 23:41.546
- CHIEF...

23:41.580 --> 23:43.684
[whispering]
YIN SENT ANOTHER CLUE.

23:44.820 --> 23:46.811
- WE HAVE THE ADDRESS.

23:46.850 --> 23:48.283
THE TIME WILL BE 9:00 PM.

23:48.320 --> 23:49.548
HE WANTS YOU ALL
TO SHOW UP THERE,

23:49.590 --> 23:51.888
WHERE HE HAS CREATED
HIS OWN MOVIE SET.

23:51.930 --> 23:53.056
- I'M DONE
WATCHING MOVIES, CHIEF.

23:53.090 --> 23:54.250
- EXACTLY, DETECTIVE.

23:54.300 --> 23:56.120
YOU NOW ARE THE MOVIE.

23:56.160 --> 23:58.390
HE'S CAST YOU ALL
AS ARCHETYPAL CHARACTERS

23:58.430 --> 23:59.966
FROM HITCHCOCK'S CANON.

24:00.000 --> 24:01.831
THERE WILL BE CLUES
THAT LEAD YOU TO CATCHING HIM,

24:01.870 --> 24:03.758
BASED ON THE PLOTS
OF THOSE FILMS.

24:03.810 --> 24:05.107
- YOU SERIOUS ABOUT THIS?

24:05.140 --> 24:06.459
WE'RE JUST SUPPOSED
TO PLAY DRESS-UP ALL NIGHT?

24:06.510 --> 24:09.070
- WE WILL DO WHATEVER IT TAKES,
DETECTIVE.

24:09.110 --> 24:11.374
HE IS GIVING US AN OPPORTUNITY
TO CATCH HIM

24:11.410 --> 24:13.105
BEFORE HE KILLS AGAIN.

24:13.150 --> 24:15.812
NOW, I'M NOT SENDING YOU
IN THERE LIKE SITTING DUCKS.

24:15.850 --> 24:17.909
HE'S MADE IT VERY CLEAR
THAT YOU ARE TO COME ALONE.

24:17.950 --> 24:20.384
BUT THE ONLY WAY THAT THIS
IS GOING TO WORK

24:20.420 --> 24:21.910
IS IF I SET UP A TEAM
ON THE OUTSIDE

24:21.960 --> 24:22.915
AND COVER THE PERIMETER.

24:22.960 --> 24:23.927
- SNIPERS?

24:23.960 --> 24:25.552
- YOU BET YOUR ASS.

24:25.590 --> 24:27.729
- KAREN...
I GOT YOUR MESSAGE.

24:27.760 --> 24:29.057
WHAT CAN I DO?

24:29.100 --> 24:30.795
- HE'S CALLED YOU OUT,
HENRY.

24:30.830 --> 24:32.024
YOU HAVE A HISTORY
WITH HIM AS WELL.

24:32.070 --> 24:34.231
- SEAN CONNERY?

24:34.270 --> 24:35.589
- DAD, YOU CAN SAY NO.

24:35.640 --> 24:36.766
- SHAWN, THE LAST TIME
THIS HAPPENED,

24:36.800 --> 24:37.903
YOU PUT YOUR LIFE
ON THE LINE.

24:37.940 --> 24:39.362
WE ALMOST LOST YOUR MOTHER.

24:39.410 --> 24:41.173
I'M GONNA BE
RIGHT BY YOUR SIDE, SON.

24:41.210 --> 24:42.279
END OF DISCUSSION.

24:43.180 --> 24:44.408
- ALL RIGHT, PEOPLE.

24:44.450 --> 24:46.805
THIS ENDS TONIGHT.

24:49.450 --> 24:51.281
- ALL RIGHT, CHIEF,
NO SIGN OF HUMAN MOVEMENT.

24:51.320 --> 24:52.981
WE'RE GONNA GAIN
A BETTER VANTAGE POINT.

24:53.020 --> 24:54.817
- OKAY, PROCEED,
BUT KEEP ME POSTED

24:54.860 --> 24:56.088
AS TO YOUR COORDINATES,

24:56.120 --> 24:58.827
AND MAKE SURE THAT EVERYONE
IS TUNED IN.

24:58.860 --> 25:01.658
SNIPERS ARE IN PLACE
AND WILL GO AT MY READY.

25:01.700 --> 25:03.497
SO NO FALSE ALARMS.

25:07.470 --> 25:09.392
I THINK THAT'S MEANT FOR ME.

25:09.440 --> 25:10.566
THAT SCENE FROM THE BIRDS--

25:10.610 --> 25:12.009
TIPPI HEDREN'S ATTACKED
IN THE CAR.

25:12.040 --> 25:13.268
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT,
LASSITER?

25:13.310 --> 25:14.572
DIDN'T YOU SEE MARNIE?

25:14.610 --> 25:16.976
HALF THAT MOVIE WAS ME AND TIPPI
DRIVING AROUND IN A CAR.

25:17.010 --> 25:18.500
THAT CLUE IS ALL ME.

25:18.550 --> 25:20.575
- YOU DO REALIZE YOU'RE NOT
ACTUALLY SEAN CONNERY, RIGHT?

25:20.620 --> 25:21.609
- OH, I'M SORRY.

25:21.650 --> 25:23.242
NO, I GOT LOST
FOR A MOMENT THERE,

25:23.280 --> 25:25.384
BECAUSE I LITERALLY THOUGHT
I WAS TALKING TO ROD TAYLOR.

25:25.420 --> 25:27.650
- WHO'S ROD TAYLOR?
- I AM!

25:27.690 --> 25:28.782
- LOOK, STOP.
WE CAN'T BE SURE.

25:28.820 --> 25:30.412
YOU SHOULD BOTH
GO AND CHECK IT OUT.

25:43.710 --> 25:45.359
- "NEED A RIDE?"

25:48.110 --> 25:49.771
- IT'S CLEAR.

25:54.820 --> 25:56.117
- ALL RIGHT,
WE'RE IN THE VEHICLE.

25:56.150 --> 25:58.038
- WATCH YOURSELF.

26:03.020 --> 26:04.089
- [imitating James Stewart]
WELL...

26:04.130 --> 26:05.427
WELL, LOOK AT THAT.

26:05.460 --> 26:08.099
THAT'S A WHEELCHAIR.

26:08.130 --> 26:09.757
UP IN THAT WINDOW THERE.

26:09.800 --> 26:10.824
- SHAWN...

26:10.870 --> 26:12.394
- AHEM.

26:12.430 --> 26:13.419
SORRY.

26:13.470 --> 26:16.268
LOOKS LIKE THAT'S MY CLUE.

26:16.300 --> 26:17.858
- BE CAREFUL.

26:19.670 --> 26:21.376
- CANADA LEE?
LIFEBOAT?

26:21.410 --> 26:23.139
DO YOU SEE
ANY WATER AROUND HERE?

26:23.180 --> 26:24.477
THERE WASN'T EVEN A PUDDLE.

26:24.510 --> 26:27.570
- YEAH, I DON'T KNOW HOW
IT FIT INTO THIS EITHER.

26:27.620 --> 26:28.575
UH, GUS...

26:28.620 --> 26:29.939
- WHAT?

26:31.920 --> 26:33.808
- MAYBE IT IS JUST A PROP.

26:33.860 --> 26:36.613
- THERE'S NO IGNITION,
NOT EVEN A PLACE FOR A KEY.

26:48.000 --> 26:49.092
- SHAWN...

26:49.140 --> 26:51.301
THIS PLACE IS CREEPY.

26:51.340 --> 26:53.365
I'M ALMOST AT THE DOOR.

26:55.540 --> 26:57.474
- OPEN IT AND THEN RUN AWAY.

27:03.420 --> 27:05.718
- IT'S LOCKED.
YIN IN SCREWING WITH US.

27:05.750 --> 27:07.240
WHAT ARE YOU SEEING?

27:07.290 --> 27:09.053
- GUS, IT'S REAR WINDOW.
I CAN SEE ALL OF YOU.

27:09.090 --> 27:10.887
I CAN SEE EVERYTHING.
THE...

27:10.930 --> 27:12.682
QUESTION IS,
WHAT ACTUALLY MATTERS?

27:15.260 --> 27:16.488
- JULES!

27:16.530 --> 27:18.669
- THAT'S ERNIE'S BAR
FROM VERTIGO!

27:18.700 --> 27:20.122
- KIM NOVAK.

27:20.170 --> 27:21.432
THIS IS ME, SHAWN.

27:21.470 --> 27:23.335
I'LL SIGNAL EVERYONE
IF THERE'S ANYTHING.

27:23.370 --> 27:26.032
- PROCEED WITH CAUTION,
DETECTIVE.

27:26.070 --> 27:28.470
- WE'RE IN A TUNNEL NOW.
HOW THE HELL'S HE DOING THIS?

27:33.110 --> 27:34.577
[music from North by Northwest
playing loudly]

27:34.620 --> 27:36.872
- AHH!
- OW!

27:36.920 --> 27:38.683
WHAT IS--WHAT IS THAT?

27:51.670 --> 27:53.592
- JULIET!

27:53.630 --> 27:55.268
- GUS...WHAT ARE YOU
DOING IN HERE?

27:55.300 --> 27:56.665
- WE CAN'T SEE YOU IN HERE.

27:56.700 --> 27:58.406
THAT MUSIC IS PLAYING SO LOUD,
WE CAN'T HEAR ANYTHING.

27:58.440 --> 28:00.135
- STAY WHERE YOU ARE.

28:00.170 --> 28:01.569
I HAVE A CLUE.

28:01.610 --> 28:04.602
"DRAUGHT US A COUPLE COLD ONES,
AND LET'S MAKE A TOAST

28:04.650 --> 28:09.178
TO YOU FALLING
HEAD OVER HEELS FOR ME."

28:09.220 --> 28:11.984
GUS. . . RELAX.

28:12.020 --> 28:13.419
IT'S WHY WE'RE HERE.

28:15.090 --> 28:16.910
I'M GOING TO DO THIS.

28:29.940 --> 28:31.362
- JULIET!

28:31.410 --> 28:33.628
- TALK TO ME.
TALK TO ME, GUS!

28:41.420 --> 28:44.412
- JULIET!

28:46.150 --> 28:49.278
- COVER YOUR EYES!
I'M GONNA SHOOT OUT THE WINDOW!

28:49.320 --> 28:50.480
[music stops]

28:55.360 --> 28:56.622
- JULIET!

28:56.660 --> 28:58.491
- SPENCER!

28:58.530 --> 28:59.724
- O'HARA, SOMEBODY--
COME IN.

28:59.770 --> 29:00.998
WHAT HAPPENED?

29:01.040 --> 29:02.792
- CAR WAS A TRAP!
WE LOST CONTACT.

29:02.840 --> 29:04.569
- SOMETHING HAPPENED
IN THE BAR!

29:04.610 --> 29:06.237
[echoing]
JULIET!

29:06.270 --> 29:07.032
JULIET!

29:08.440 --> 29:11.568
[police radio]
ALL UNITS BE ON THE
LOOKOUT FOR DETECTIVE O'HARA.

29:11.610 --> 29:15.717
[police radio]
IN CUSTODY OF SUSPECT MR. YIN.
SUSPECT IS ARMED AND DANGEROUS.

29:15.750 --> 29:18.947
[police radio]
APPROACH WITH CAUTION.

29:28.230 --> 29:30.494
- I KNOW THIS IS HARD.

29:30.530 --> 29:32.725
WE'RE READY TO TAKE THE CALL
WHEN IT COMES IN.

29:32.770 --> 29:33.759
THERE'S NOTHING MORE
WE CAN DO.

29:33.800 --> 29:35.836
- IT'S MY FAULT.

29:35.870 --> 29:38.065
- DAMMIT, SPENCER,
THIS IS NOT YOUR FAULT.

29:38.110 --> 29:40.328
DETECTIVE O'HARA
WAS MY RESPONSIBILITY.

29:40.370 --> 29:42.577
THAT TUNNEL WASN'T ON
ANY OF THE SCHEMATICS,

29:42.610 --> 29:43.736
AND THE SON OF A BITCH
KNEW IT.

29:43.780 --> 29:45.077
THERE'S NO WAY
WE COULD HAVE KNOWN.

29:45.110 --> 29:48.409
- UNLESS YOU'RE A PSYCHIC.

29:48.450 --> 29:49.678
- SHAWN...

29:49.720 --> 29:50.846
I JUST SPOKE
WITH YOUR MOTHER.

29:50.890 --> 29:52.517
I WANTED HER TO KNOW
THAT YOU WERE SAFE.

29:52.550 --> 29:53.744
SHE'S FINE.

29:53.790 --> 29:56.258
SHE'S AT A HOTEL IN NEW YORK
AT A CONFERENCE.

29:56.290 --> 29:58.429
I TOLD HER TO STAY PUT.

29:58.460 --> 29:59.927
- SHAWN...

29:59.960 --> 30:01.598
DOESN'T ABIGAIL
GET IN TONIGHT?

30:04.170 --> 30:05.421
- OH, MY GOD.

30:05.470 --> 30:07.358
WHAT TIME IS IT?

30:07.400 --> 30:08.958
- IT'S ALMOST 1:00.

30:09.000 --> 30:10.592
- HER FLIGHT GETS IN
IN HALF AN HOUR.

30:10.640 --> 30:12.938
- WE CAN'T AFFORD
TO LET YOU GO.

30:12.970 --> 30:14.369
SHAWN, WHAT HAPPENS
IF A CALL COMES IN

30:14.410 --> 30:16.071
AND WE NEED TO BE SOMEWHERE
HALFWAY ACROSS THE CITY

30:16.110 --> 30:17.839
IN 11 MINUTES?
- I HAVE TO PICK HER UP.

30:17.880 --> 30:18.904
- DON'T WORRY.

30:18.950 --> 30:21.168
WE'LL SEND SOMEONE TO GET HER.
SOMEONE SHE KNOWS.

30:24.350 --> 30:25.749
MCNAB!

30:28.360 --> 30:29.679
- HOW WAS UGANDA?

30:29.720 --> 30:31.620
- IT WAS RICH, COMPELLING,
A MUST-SEE.

30:31.660 --> 30:32.820
WHAT IS THIS ABOUT, BUZZ?

30:32.860 --> 30:34.122
- CAN'T REALLY SAY.

30:34.160 --> 30:35.650
I'M JUST HERE TO MAKE SURE
YOU GET HOME SAFELY.

30:35.700 --> 30:37.258
- WHY WOULDN'T I BE SAFE?

30:37.300 --> 30:39.222
THIS IS RIDICULOUS,
AND I AM BEYOND JETLAGGED.

30:39.270 --> 30:41.738
JUST TELL ME
WHAT IS GOING ON.

30:41.770 --> 30:43.465
- PLEASE, MS. LYTAR.

30:43.500 --> 30:45.263
JUST FOLLOWING MY ORDERS.

30:47.470 --> 30:49.938
- "MS. LYTAR"?

30:49.980 --> 30:51.447
REALLY?

30:58.390 --> 31:00.381
- BUZZ, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

31:01.290 --> 31:03.713
- OH, MY GOD!
ARE YOU OKAY?

31:03.760 --> 31:05.182
[screams]

31:06.560 --> 31:09.529
BUZZ!
SOMEBODY HELP ME!

31:09.560 --> 31:11.118
NO!

31:13.070 --> 31:14.765
[cell phone ringing]

31:14.800 --> 31:16.131
- IT'S ABIGAIL.

31:16.170 --> 31:18.229
HEY, ABS, SORRY I COULDN'T
PICK YOU UP MYSELF.

31:18.270 --> 31:19.339
- [whispering] HELLO, SHAWN.

31:19.370 --> 31:22.032
I HAVE GOOD NEWS
AND BAD NEWS.

31:22.080 --> 31:23.069
[turns on speaker phone]
THE GOOD NEWS IS

31:23.110 --> 31:24.748
THAT OUR FEMME FATALE

31:24.780 --> 31:26.202
IS STILL VERY MUCH ALIVE.

31:26.250 --> 31:28.115
THE BAD NEWS,
FOR YOU ANYWAY,

31:28.150 --> 31:31.187
IS THAT I HAVE NOW MET
THE GIRL NEXT DOOR.

31:31.220 --> 31:32.778
I UNDERSTAND YOUR PREDICAMENT.

31:32.820 --> 31:35.254
THEY'RE BOTH SO YOU.

31:35.290 --> 31:37.952
BUT WE CAN'T HAVE
OUR CAKE AND EAT IT TOO.

31:37.990 --> 31:40.129
SO I'M DOING YOU
A FAVOR HERE

31:40.160 --> 31:42.299
BY FORCING YOU TO CHOOSE.

31:42.330 --> 31:43.251
- CHOOSE?

31:43.300 --> 31:44.597
- YES, SHAWN.

31:44.630 --> 31:46.598
WHO DO YOU
CARE ABOUT MORE?

31:46.630 --> 31:49.497
BECAUSE YOU CAN'T
SAVE THEM BOTH.

32:04.190 --> 32:06.078
- MCNAB IS OKAY.

32:06.120 --> 32:08.953
HE DIDN'T GET A LOOK
AT YIN.

32:10.360 --> 32:12.555
YOU WANT SOMETHING
FROM THE SNACK MACHINE?

32:12.590 --> 32:14.797
YOU KNOW, THEY HAVE BUGLES.

32:20.570 --> 32:22.561
[cell phone ringing]

32:22.600 --> 32:26.161
THIS IS IT!
THIS IS IT!

32:29.340 --> 32:32.207
WHAT IS THE CLUE?
WHAT'S THE CLUE!

32:32.250 --> 32:35.742
- SHAWN, I'LL DROP BY
HALF PAST 4:00.

32:35.780 --> 32:38.089
MY HANDS ARE ON MY FACE.

32:38.120 --> 32:40.486
PLEASE COME QUICK,
OR THIS COULD BE MESSY.

32:40.520 --> 32:41.555
SHAWN, YOU CAN STILL
SAVE ABIGAI--

32:41.590 --> 32:43.581
[dial tone]

32:58.970 --> 33:00.733
- "HANDS ON MY FACE."
IT'S A CLOCK.

33:00.770 --> 33:02.874
- HALF PAST FOUR,
THIS COULD GET MESSY.

33:02.910 --> 33:04.309
- "I'LL DROP BY."

33:04.350 --> 33:06.306
- SHE'S KIM NOVAK
IN VERTIGO.

33:06.350 --> 33:08.671
- "I'LL...DROP BY."

33:08.720 --> 33:10.608
- INSTEAD OF A BELL TOWER...
- IT'S A CLOCK TOWER.

33:10.650 --> 33:12.015
IT'S THE CLOCK TOWER!

33:12.050 --> 33:13.119
- DETECTIVE, WAIT.

33:13.150 --> 33:14.959
A CIVILIAN HAS BEEN
TAKEN AS WELL.

33:14.990 --> 33:16.412
SHE MUST BE GIVEN PRIORITY.

33:16.460 --> 33:17.779
IF WE HAD
THE SLIGHTEST CLUE--

33:17.820 --> 33:19.082
- YOU'VE GOT
OTHER UNITS, CHIEF.

33:19.130 --> 33:20.984
I'LL BE GOING
TO GET MY PARTNER NOW.

33:21.030 --> 33:22.395
- DETECTIVE!

33:22.430 --> 33:23.658
MR. SPENCER,

33:23.700 --> 33:25.998
CAN YOU TELL US
WHERE ABIGAIL IS?

33:29.340 --> 33:31.365
- I CAN'T.

33:31.410 --> 33:33.469
THERE'S NO WAY
TO SAVE THEM BOTH.

33:35.710 --> 33:36.904
[sniffles]

33:37.780 --> 33:39.145
IT'S JULES.

33:39.180 --> 33:40.579
WE KNOW WHERE SHE IS,
WE FOLLOW LASSIE.

33:40.610 --> 33:42.919
WE SAVE JULIET.

33:42.950 --> 33:45.089
- OKAY.

33:45.120 --> 33:46.815
I'LL DRIVE.

33:46.850 --> 33:48.488
HENRY, GO HOME.

33:48.520 --> 33:49.748
YOUR ROLE HERE IS FINISHED.

33:49.790 --> 33:51.155
- NOT A CHANCE IN HELL.

33:51.190 --> 33:52.726
- YOU, TOO, ARE A CIVILIAN,

33:52.760 --> 33:54.921
AND THEREFORE
AN UNNECESSARY RISK.

33:54.960 --> 33:57.622
- ALL RIGHT, I ACCEPT.
- EXCUSE ME?

33:57.660 --> 33:59.218
- THE JOB--THE JOB
YOU OFFERED ME, KAREN.

33:59.270 --> 34:00.294
I ACCEPT.

34:00.330 --> 34:02.389
CUT ME A LITTLE SLACK
ON THE WARDROBE.

34:02.440 --> 34:04.431
IT'S GREAT TO BE BACK.

34:06.210 --> 34:07.700
- GUS, WAIT.

34:10.040 --> 34:12.270
THE COVER.

34:12.310 --> 34:14.449
YANG DIDN'T DRAW HERSELF.

34:14.480 --> 34:17.210
SHE DREW ABIGAIL...
ON THE PIER.

34:17.250 --> 34:18.808
I THINK I KNOW WHERE SHE IS.
- LET'S GO GET HER.

34:18.850 --> 34:20.112
- NO, NO, NO.
I COULD BE WRONG.

34:20.150 --> 34:21.754
YOU GO WITH THE CHIEF.
YOU HELP LASSIE.

34:21.790 --> 34:23.052
- SHAWN, YOU'RE NOT
GOING ALONE.

34:23.090 --> 34:24.819
- GUS, THE ONLY WAY THAT
I CAN NOT BE THERE FOR JULIET

34:24.860 --> 34:26.452
IS IF I KNOW THAT YOU ARE.

34:26.490 --> 34:28.151
AND I WON'T BE ALONE.

34:36.240 --> 34:38.128
BOATS.

34:38.170 --> 34:39.706
- ALL RIGHT,
DON'T WORRY, SON.

34:39.740 --> 34:41.378
IF SHE'S HERE,
WE'LL FIND HER.

34:58.190 --> 35:00.556
- SHE'S UNDER THE PIER,
ISN'T SHE?

35:15.310 --> 35:17.471
[grunting]

35:17.510 --> 35:18.807
I SEE YOU, SWEETHEART.

35:18.850 --> 35:20.909
BLINK ONCE FOR YES,
AND TWO FOR NO.

35:20.950 --> 35:22.815
ARE THERE ANY EXPLOSIVES
THAT I CAN TRIGGER

35:22.850 --> 35:23.874
BY COMING IN?

35:25.550 --> 35:27.780
[panï¬ng]

35:33.990 --> 35:35.423
- SHAWN!

35:41.000 --> 35:42.536
- OH, YOU'RE KIDDING ME!

35:42.570 --> 35:43.696
- OKAY, TAKE THE STAIRS.

35:43.740 --> 35:45.605
I'LL MAN THE POINT
AND SET UP A PERIMETER.

35:45.640 --> 35:48.302
- [gasping for air]

35:48.340 --> 35:49.500
HEY.
- HEY.

35:49.540 --> 35:51.178
- WE'VE REALLY COME
FULL CIRCLE, HUH?

35:51.210 --> 35:52.973
THIS IS WHERE I STOOD YOU UP
ON OUR FIRST DATE.

35:53.010 --> 35:54.318
- THANKS FOR SHOWING UP
THIS TIME.

35:54.350 --> 35:55.476
- AHH.

35:55.520 --> 35:56.669
- HEY, ABBY.

35:56.720 --> 35:58.073
HOW WAS YOUR TRIP?

35:58.120 --> 35:59.109
- AWESOME!

35:59.150 --> 36:00.686
- IT'S JUST ROPE!

36:00.720 --> 36:02.483
PLEASE TELL ME
YOU STILL CARRY YOUR SWISS.

36:02.520 --> 36:03.657
- OF COURSE I DO.

36:03.690 --> 36:05.123
I TAUGHT YOU THAT.

36:05.160 --> 36:06.422
- COME ON IN!
THE WATER'S GREAT!

36:08.830 --> 36:10.957
YOU JUST CONCENTRATE
ON YOUR BREATHING.

36:11.000 --> 36:12.627
I PROMISE NOT TO TRY ANYTHING
WHILE I'M DOWN THERE.

36:12.670 --> 36:13.659
[big inhale]

36:21.340 --> 36:22.773
- IT'S GETTING HIGHER!

36:29.220 --> 36:31.484
HURRY!
[gasplng]

36:35.060 --> 36:36.948
[both gasping]

36:36.990 --> 36:38.480
- WE'RE ALMOST THERE.
- OKAY.

36:38.530 --> 36:39.952
- WE'RE ALMOST THERE.

36:53.110 --> 36:55.738
- O'HARA!
MY GOD.

36:55.780 --> 36:56.906
ALL RIGHT, DON'T WORRY.

36:56.940 --> 36:57.975
WE'LL GET YOU OUT OF THIS!

36:58.010 --> 36:58.999
[bzz]
-AHH!

36:59.050 --> 37:01.814
- GAH! NO!

37:11.290 --> 37:14.054
- YOU GOTTA DO SOMETHING, QUICK!
I CAN'T HOLD IT FOR LONG!

37:14.090 --> 37:15.250
[grunting loudly]

37:18.800 --> 37:20.597
UHH! AHH! OHH!

37:23.900 --> 37:26.630
-AAH! UHH!

37:34.650 --> 37:35.776
AAAAH!

37:40.120 --> 37:41.610
- GOOD WORK!

37:43.360 --> 37:45.828
WE GOT YOU.
WE GOT YOU.

37:46.960 --> 37:49.724
[all grunting and gasping]

37:49.760 --> 37:51.569
- ALL RIGHT.
- YOU ALL RIGHT?

37:51.600 --> 37:52.919
- OKAY. UHH!

37:52.970 --> 37:54.289
- OHH.

37:54.340 --> 37:58.037
[cell phone ringing]

37:58.070 --> 38:00.129
[beep]

38:00.170 --> 38:02.070
GUS.
- SHAWN.

38:02.110 --> 38:03.304
WE GOT HER.

38:03.340 --> 38:04.705
IT WAS CLOSE,
BUT WE GOT HER.

38:04.750 --> 38:05.705
SHE'S OKAY.

38:05.750 --> 38:07.240
- GOD.

38:07.280 --> 38:08.417
THANK GOD.

38:08.450 --> 38:10.418
OH, THANK GOD.

38:10.450 --> 38:12.611
ABIGAIL'S OKAY TOO.
SHE'S GOOD.

38:12.650 --> 38:14.311
- OHH.

38:15.490 --> 38:16.809
- GUS, HE WAS HERE.

38:16.860 --> 38:18.589
I SAW HIM.

38:18.630 --> 38:20.052
I COULD HAVE TOUCHED HIM.

38:20.090 --> 38:21.921
BUT I HAD TO LET HIM GO.

38:21.960 --> 38:24.292
- YOU HAD NO CHOICE.

38:24.330 --> 38:26.696
YOU DID THE RIGHT THING.

38:26.730 --> 38:29.597
- YOU KNOW, THIS GAME
ISN'T OVER.

38:29.640 --> 38:33.064
- I KNOW.

38:33.110 --> 38:35.931
_ THANKS FOR BEING THERE,
BUDDY.

38:35.980 --> 38:37.106
[beep]

38:41.780 --> 38:43.247
UHH!

38:43.280 --> 38:44.611
JULIET'S OKAY.

38:44.650 --> 38:46.743
- GOOD. GOOD.

38:46.790 --> 38:50.089
LISTEN, YOU TAKE CARE
OF YOUR GIRL.

38:50.120 --> 38:51.849
I'LL GO TALK TO THE COPS.

38:51.890 --> 38:54.825
ALL RIGHT?
- YEAH.

38:54.860 --> 38:57.124
- HOW 'BOUT THE SWISS, HUH?

38:57.160 --> 38:59.424
- NEVER LEAVE HOME
WITHOUT IT.

38:59.470 --> 39:01.097
- NO, I MEAN, UH...

39:01.130 --> 39:02.791
I THINK YOU'VE GOT MY KNIFE.
I'VE GOT YOURS.

39:02.840 --> 39:05.138
- OH!
DID WE GET SWITCHED UP?

39:05.170 --> 39:06.535
- YEAH.

39:06.570 --> 39:08.208
- OH, YEAH, LOOK AT THAT.

39:08.240 --> 39:10.435
GOD, YOURS IS SO MUCH
BIGGER THAN MINE.

39:14.280 --> 39:15.679
WOW.

39:19.750 --> 39:21.149
both: THAN KS.

